title: 35 MIN FULL BODY WORKOUT || Intermediate Mat Pilates (No Equipment)

channelDescription:
Hi, I'm Nicole! 😊 I am a Certified Pilates & Certified Yoga Instructor (RYT 500) with many years of in-studio teaching experience. As a former dancer and gymnast, I have always had a passion for movement and I love being able to share that passion with others. I believe in finding forms of movement that feel good for your body and soul and I hope that through my classes, I can guide you to your best feeling self!

--
I was a professional Latin Ballroom Dancer and taught Ballroom dancing to adults for 7+ years. This is truly where I established my passion for teaching movement. When I retired from competitive dancing in 2017, I began teaching Barre and Pilates in studios and gyms in Sydney.

During COVID lockdown, Dance & Pilates studios closed and that was when I poured my love of teaching into this channel, hoping to help people keep moving and feeling good!

Thank you so much for practicing with me and I hope you enjoy the classes as much as I love creating them for you. 🩷

comments: Oh my gosh. The swan dive is on different level. Tried to do it just for the feel of it.. Nicole looked so elegant meanwhile I literally look like a fish struggling out of water. 😂 Another added to the list of poses that I am aiming to perform as elegant as I could.. Thank you Nicole! ❤

Nicole, you're the best. My wife and I have been doing your videos for the last year or so. We love your style, calm yet challenging and reassuring. Your guidance is unparalleled. Also we love your new cat.
I've been doing your exercises for 6 months and I feel a huge difference with my body. Thanks you so much for everything, you are great, don't stop doing new videos  please :)

So grateful for your videos, you’ve taught me that “working out” doesn’t have to feel like pushing my body to excruciating limits. That it can be a healing practice of breathing and mindfulness!! Thank you!!!!

Just finished this workout so many new movements, it was not easy but I love it! I feel like I’m part of a big family when I hear “well deserved child’s pose” or “let’s finish class like always”. Mantra in its own! Thank you Nicole xx
